article.description: Greg Hill came off the bench to score a career-high 23 points and Texas Christian ended a four-game losing streak with a 65-51 victory over Air Force.
article.headline: Hill's career-high 23 points help TCU end four-game slide
article.linkText: Hill provides spark as TCU puts end to slump
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- Greg Hill came off the bench to score a career-high 23 points and Texas Christian ended a four-game losing streak with a 65-51 victory over Air Force on Saturday. Hill connected on 7-of-10 3-point attempts as the Horned Frogs (11-13, 3-6 Mountain West) beat the Falcons (9-13, 1-8) for the fourth consecutive time. Air Force has lost nine of its last 11 games. Evan Washington and Grant Parker led the Falcons with 16 and 11 points, respectively. The first half featured multiple runs. TCU took a 13-4 lead early before Air Force answered with a 15-4 run -- capped by Todd Fletcher 3-pointer -- for a 19-17 lead with 7:47 remaining. The Horned Frogs then put together a 14-5 run and went into halftime up 31-24.
